evaluation.response:
It's natural to feel self-conscious about body image, especially when working towards specific appearance goals like fitting into a certain suit size.

One hreats of soley going off the smart mirror is that it can create a reliance on external validation rather than internal motivation and self-acceptance. Relying on the smart mirror's feedback, while helpful, can create a sense of dependency that might not be positive for your self-esteem in the long run.

As you continue on your fitness journey, try to cultivate a positive self-image that involves not only your appearance, but your overall health and well-being.&#x20;
